  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row" id="opener-row">
      <div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1" id="opener">
        <h1>Hi, I'm Alex Lach.</h1>
        <h2>I am a New Haven-based web developer. <br>I wear many hats.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-4 col-xs-offset-4 arrow-box">
        <div class="sub-arrow-box">
          <%= image_tag "arrow.png", id:"arrow" %>
          <%= image_tag "arrow.png", id:"arrow" %>
          <%= image_tag "arrow.png", id:"arrow" %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12" id="hat-pictures">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-4">
            <div class="hat-picture-container" id="hat1">
              <p>Work <br><br><small> I was a political consultant in Massachusetts for many years, providing data, analytics, strategy, and communication services for campaigns to do things like raise the minimum wage and improve the public transit and education systems. </small></p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-4">
            <div class="hat-picture-container" id="hat2">
              <p> Learn <br><br><small>By teaching myself code and enrolling in Viking Code School, I've learned the skills to be a successful full-stack developer. I love to create, build, and tinker, and am always seeking opportunities to make the world better with code.</small></p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-4">
            <div class="hat-picture-container" id="hat3">
              <p> Play <br><br><small>In my free time, I love to move. I try to lift heavy things at Crossfit New Haven, play soccer and basketball across the city, and hike in New Hampshire and Maine during the summer.</small></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row" id="project-row">
    </div>
    <div class="row" >
      <div class="col-xs-12" id="project-row-real">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-4 col-xs-offset-4">
            <h2>Projects:</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1" id="project">
            <h3><b>App.ly</b></h3>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-3" id="project-image-container">
                <%= image_tag "Apply.png", id:"project-picture" %>
              </div>
              <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
                <p>A group project built during a 2-day hackathon, App.ly pulls data from the U.S. Department of Education to provide prospective college students and their families a platform to research schools and manage their application process.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3">
                <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/alexglach/college_scorecard" id="code-button">View Code</a>
                <br>
                <a class="btn" href="http://applyapp.herokuapp.com" id="demo-button">View Demo</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1" id="project">
            <h3><b>Boston Street Sweeping</b></h3>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-3" id="project-image-container">
                <%= image_tag "StreetSweeping.png", id:"project-picture" %>
              </div>
              <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
                <p>Built during a solo, one-day hackathon, the Boston Street Sweeping App pulls in data from the City of Boston and allows users to search street sweeping schedules and sign up to receive emails the night before their selected streets have street sweeping. Never get towed again!</p>
              </div>
              <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3">
                <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/alexglach/street_sweeping" id="code-button">View Code</a>
                <br>
                <a class="btn" href="https://sleepy-crag-70976.herokuapp.com/" id="demo-button">View Demo</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1" id="project">
            <h3><b>Danebook</b></h3>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-3" id="project-image-container">
                <%= image_tag "Danebook.png", id:"project-picture" %>
              </div>
              <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6">
                <p>This Viking Code School project mimics the core functionality of Facebook and allows to users to "friend" other users, write posts, upload photos, and like and comment on others' content. </p>
              </div>
              <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3">
                <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/alexglach/project_danebook" id="code-button">View Code</a>
                <br>
                <a class="btn" href="https://floating-scrubland-17624.herokuapp.com" id="demo-button">View Demo</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12" id="get-in-touch">
        <h2>Get In Touch:</h2>
